  <notes>
  <p>
  This beer is inspired by Fuller's London Pride.  It's by no means
  a clone (in fact it tastes very different).  But it's a very
  pleasant pale ale.  The first thing that's noticable is that
  the character of the Fuggles and Goldings hops comes through
  nicely.  It's got a nice bitterness to it.  If it's missing
  anything it's on the malt side.  I think a different yeast
  would be needed to improve things.  However, this is a very
  pleasant beer.  Can drink a lot of these.
  </p>
